			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3948')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=43751860&M_NAME=Alaaraaf')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=43751860&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Alaaraaf an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=13321&TOPIC_ID=1882&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Why+are+ubers+bitching+about+focus+items%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hey.</P><P>The original argument was about complete heal.  With the focuses, you could shave twenty percent off the casting time.  <i>(And twenty percent off the mana cost.  But that's not the big deal here.)</i>  Most, if not all the big encounters are handled by a whole bunch of clerics whacking the designated Main Tank with complete heal every few seconds.  The focus means you can do the encounter with twenty percent less clerics!  <i>(Cool, huh?)</i></P><P>The bitch is that this makes complete heal too powerful.  <i>(You will hear a good many arguments that it is too powerful even without the focus.  *Shrug*)</i>  Personally, I have no problems with it, since healing is what clerics do.  <i>(I mean, how exciting is being a cleric, really?)</i></P><P>The reason for the Uber guilds being unhappy, is that you have to collect up a lot of powerful people for the big encounters.  Since they are predominantly sucking up all these people, it means it is difficult for anyone else to compete for the big mobs.  There is a threat however, if another guild can cut their overheads by twenty percent, that this small, upstart guild might be able to kill an uber mob.  This is like stealing, because the uber mobs <b>belong</b> to the uber guilds.</P><P>As for the focus items being better than the likes of NToV loot...  Well, there's almost some validity to this.  <i>(Socking, huh?)</i>  If your gear is so hot you don't miss the empty slot, it is better.  If I have a Blue Diamond bracer and I replace it with a focus bracer, the deal is, 'Is the focus effect better than the resistances I'm losing?'  If I'm not being hit by AE spells, or even better, not being hit by anything, quite possibly.  If, on the other hand, you're fighting something that can only be cast upon from within melee range, probably not.  <i>(More damage <b>is</b> good.  But you have to stay alive to cast.)</i></P><P>The real problem was possibly not the power of the items, but the availablilty.  A twenty percent casting haste, is as good to a caster and an FBSS to a warrior.  But, since the focus just cost some mana, they're pretty easy to come by.  <i>(Especially while they're new and everyone is playing with 'em.)</i>  Imagine the bitchin' if tomorrow mages could summon items with twenty percent haste and damage for melees.  It's the same thing.  <i>(I'd be willing to gamble that there were more focuses in play before the repatching, than there were FBSS's.)</i></P><P>The last issue, is that mages major issue in the upcoming balancing is that they summon a ton of great stuff, before a fight and then have no role.  Focuses don't fix this.  It's another real good thing they can summon.  But once they've done their thing,they're still either standing and watching, or being told to log in a more useful character, for the battle itself.</P><P>Anyhow, hope this helps.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
