        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> The thing that makes no sense is nothing changed. Sure some casters got a few more points on their DDs and Clerics *had the chance*(remember, its not every cast is at max damage/castime, etc. It was a chance that it would do 1% to 20%, 15% concerning the CH problem) to land a CH in 8.5 seconds rather than 10. Its really not that big a deal when you think about it. The amount of fights lost because of a matter of 1.5 seconds is probably minuscule. So nothing REALLY changed in a big way. </P><P>The uber guilds complained that all of a sudden, mobs that they have been killing for years are suddenly trivialized. First off, how the hell do they know? They kill these kinds of mobs like clockwork, and as easy as tying their shoes. Especially on a server where one major guild has control over such spawns. They kill them at their leisure and with little trouble to begin with. So suddenly these focus items take all their fun out of the game...soooo...dont use the focus items if the challenge is eating you up that bad. </P><P>The real problem for the ubers was that these items were summoned by Mages and ANYONE could get one and potentially increase their damage, healing, buffing output/efficiency. Notice theres the potential again, meaning that these werent at set rates, it was a percentage based item. But the ubers didnt like it regardless. They want things like this all to themselves. How dare some level 51 caster actually get a possible 10% increase in a nuke! And all he had to do was ask his neighborhood mage...>gasp!< Oh dear God no! He didnt sit in some zone picking his ass for 20 hours straight with 40 other people all doing the same thing just to get the item. I have to say after reading a few of the responses from some of the FoH people, I gotta laugh. Especially Furor...this guy has figured out a way of bitching and moaning about how he and his guild deserve everything and everyone else should get nothing. He knows how to make it sound like a game issue, when its really not. Other than his really mindnumbingly bad spelling, hes really pretty smart to work his whine in such a way that it sounds as if its a game destroying feature to have focus items.</P><P>Just wait til Vulak or THO or Ssra drop their first focus item with a 40 to 50% increase for casters. You wont hear shit outta the ubers after that.</P><P><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/sig00b.jpg" border=0></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
