        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hey.</P><P>The thing I maybe shoulda commented on, is that for a number of the biggest uber guilds, many of the huge encounters are pretty trivial.  They take time and effort, but they're pretty much a sure thing.  Go check out some of the really high end stuff on Allakhazams.  Some of these mobs drop stuff that's incredible.</P><P>So, at the moment, they have this stuff.  It's theirs, as soon as the mob pops.  All they gotta do is march in and collect it.  But, if the encounter is made a bit easier, someone else can go and collect their toys.  This is the reason for bitching.  </P><P>Imagine you and I have a server to ourselves.  I have a level fifty-one necromancer and you have a level Forty-Three necromacer.  We both want something from a mob, but I can kill it and you can't.  I can leave that mob popped for a week and when I go back to it, it'll be there.  And I can take the item.  And I'm happy.  But now, you get a focus and now you can kill him too.  So now, I have to get there before you.  If I was a nice person, I'd be happy for you and tell ya you did well.  But, if I'm an obsessive psychopath whose whole existence revolves around playing EverQuest seventy hours a week, in order to monopolise that mob, I'm gonna say it's not fair.</P><P><i>(You know how you can walk inside the models in EQ?  Walk inside an uber mob.  They all have little tags that say, 'Assembled in Taiwan.  Property of Uber_Guild_002'!  Seriously!  *Evil grin*)</i></P><P>Anyhow, don't believe all the bitching.  Verant didn't nerf the focuses because of Furor, or anyone else.  The bitching is stupidity, but it's also irrelevant, unless it's en masse.</P><P>The simple fact is, Verant don't care what you, I, or any other individual thinks, wants, or cares about.  The aim is upset the least number of people, the least amount.  There will always be a small number of people unhappy about any change.  The idea is to maximise the playerbase.  If they could do this, by removing DoTs and necromancer pets, then they'd go at the next patch.  This is reality.</P><P>Profit is God.</P><P>*Shrug*</P><P>Can't argue wit' that!</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
